metadata.name: HASH*W1NDOWS #56
metadata.description:
HASH*W1NDOWS made in PICO-8. 
Window tribute to John Karel by Y Griega.

Features:
51 Elements(6 rare).
32 Base Colours (4 layers)
12 Background Textures (3 layers).
4 Window views.

Rare Features:
+ Dark Palette (warm)
+ Death Palette (negative)
+  Fx (flys, glitch, etc...)

metadata.name: Hello World #103
metadata.description:
With this token, I am entering a new chapter in making generative art. 

I recorded myself saying "Hello World" and converted the sound file to a set of amplitudes extracted from my voice. That set of amplitudes was then used to create a rotating set of discs that are orbiting a "Sun". 

As the system is rotating, the details of a generative overlay can be seen more clearly. This overlay is also a sneak peak into my next artwork coming soon.

Press keys 1-4 to change the view, press "F" to toggle framerate between 60 and 30.

metadata.name: Spinner Playground #99
metadata.description:
This is the first creation from Kakashii.tez!

These pieces were generated all through javascript code and allow the user to interact with their token using their mouse to make their spinner move however they want! The user is also able to hit the "S" key at any point to take a SpinnerShot screenshot!

These pieces have four different features attached to them:
- Segment_Amount: The number of segments a spinner has. (min: 3, max: 50)
- Segment_Weight: The size of each segment of a spinner. (min: 8, max: 60)
- Separation: The distance between segments of a spinner. (min: 1, max: 5)
- Rarity_Score: How rare a spinner is based off of features, higher is better! (min: 175 max: 2000)

I hope you all enjoy minting your very own spinner, hope the hash rarities are on your side, and above all; have fun at the Spinner Playground!

Interaction Notes:
- Use your mouse to control your spinner.
- Press the "S" key to take a screenshot of your spinner.

metadata.name: Bløbs #32
metadata.description:
These Bløbs take on different shapes and grow a different amount and type of eyes. Ideal to use as a profile picture. 

A fun generative project to steer away from the "computer aesthetic" and experiment with a more illustrative style. No pre-rendered assets where used.
